The paper focuses on the development support for answer-set programming (ASP) and proposes a dedicated annotation language called LANA to augment answer-set programs with additional meta-information. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Programming Languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper discusses tools for documentation, testing, and verification purposes, which are relevant to Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also mentions an integrated development environment for ASP, which falls under the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
